==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Harmonics
<hw>Har*mon"ics</hw> <pr>(-⟦icr⟧ks)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The doctrine or science of musical sounds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>Secondary and
less distinct tones which accompany any principal, and apparently
simple, tone, as the octave, the twelfth, the fifteenth, and the
seventeenth. The name is also applied to the artificial tones produced
by a string or column of air, when the impulse given to it suffices only
to make a part of the string or column vibrate; overtones.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harmonious</ent>⟦br⟧
